reviews.text: I went there with my friends for lunch and we ordered paella, suckling pig and cod fish set. We're all surprised by the bread, appetizer, the main dish (of course) and the dessert! It cost around $200 each which might look a bit pricey but the quality spoke for itself. What a feast! Highly recommended!
Good Spanish food. I liked their Margarita. Good sausage, rice and roast pig.
We ordered many different dishes. Overall quality is quite good… well, except the oysters are so-so . Some of the waiting staff are not happy working there. Otherwise, I will give 4 stars.
Good quality and reasonable price. Very close to mrt station.
